#. type: Plain text
#: docs/dev/50.packaging/60.advanced/50.hooks.mdx:6
msgid ""
"YunoHost includes a hook mechanism triggered on a lot of operation changing "
"the system. You can use this mechanism in order to extend the behaviour of a "
"YunoHost command."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/dev/50.packaging/60.advanced/50.hooks.mdx:8
msgid ""
"The most obvious case is adding a user. If you had a `post_user_create` "
"hook, this hook will be triggered as soon as a user is added."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: docs/dev/50.packaging/60.advanced/50.hooks.mdx:9
#, no-wrap
msgid "How to add a custom hook on a specific instance"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced div block (tip)
#: docs/dev/50.packaging/60.advanced/50.hooks.mdx:11
#, no-wrap
msgid "Below we imagine we want to run a command after each user creation to add the user to samba user.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/dev/50.packaging/60.advanced/50.hooks.mdx:16
msgid ""
"You should create a directory with the name of the hooks into `/etc/yunohost/"
"hooks.d/`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (bash)
#: docs/dev/50.packaging/60.advanced/50.hooks.mdx:17
#, no-wrap
msgid "mkdir -p /etc/yunohost/hooks.d/post_user_create\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/dev/50.packaging/60.advanced/50.hooks.mdx:22
msgid ""
"Next create a bash script inside this directory prefixed by 2 numbers and a "
"dash:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (bash)
#: docs/dev/50.packaging/60.advanced/50.hooks.mdx:23
#, no-wrap
msgid "nano /etc/yunohost/hooks.d/post_user_create/05-add-user-to-samba\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/dev/50.packaging/60.advanced/50.hooks.mdx:28
msgid ""
"By default, the directory must be readable and traversable by root, but if "
"you notice your hook is not run at all by YunoHost, you can check "
"permissions with `ls -l /etc/yunohost/hooks.d/` and apply these commands if "
"needed:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (bash)
#: docs/dev/50.packaging/60.advanced/50.hooks.mdx:29
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"chown root:root /etc/yunohost/hooks.d/post_user_create\n"
"chmod u+rx /etc/yunohost/hooks.d/post_user_create\n"
msgstr ""

